My problem with all this is that the whole monetization thing is being used as an excuse to label us creators as administrators, when we’re really just users who can only do what YouTube allows us to. It’s their platform, their algorithms, their Terms of Service, their flawed business model, their screw up, etc.

P.s. I think Dan’s solution is brilliant, we don’t have to solve the “users not administrators” issue if it doesn’t exist. I look forward to hearing about the results of his interview with YouTube.

snippet.textDisplay: I don't know if Dan thought about this, but even with his solution, there will be some people who just don't log in. How will Youtube be able to justify whether that viewer is under 13 or not? Both people who are 13 and older, as well as under 13 use this feature all the time. The only solution I see to this issue is that they remove it completely, and only allow people to view Youtube videos by logging into an account. But if they do remove this option, it will greatly increase the time it takes for someone to watch a video if they aren't logged in, and cause a large inconvenience for the viewer. I don't know about this, but let me know what Dan, and everyone else things about this thought.
